==Events==
*  [[70]] &amp;ndash; The [[destruction of the Second Temple]] in [[Jerusalem]] by the [[Roman Empire|Romans]].
* [[367]] &amp;ndash; [[Gratian]], son of [[Roman Emperor]] [[Valentinian I]], is named co-[[Augustus (honorific)|Augustus]] by his father and associated to the throne aged eight.
*[[1265]] &amp;ndash; [[Second Barons' War]]: [[Battle of Evesham]] &amp;ndash; the army of Prince Edward (the future king [[Edward I of England]]) defeats the forces of rebellious barons led by [[Simon de Montfort, 6th Earl of Leicester]], killing de Montfort and many of his allies.
*[[1532]] &amp;ndash; the [[Duchy of Brittany]] is annexed to the [[Kingdom of France]].
*[[1578]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Al Kasr al Kebir]] &amp;ndash; the [[Moroccans]] defeat the [[Portugal|Portuguese]]. King [[Sebastian of Portugal]] is killed in the battle, leaving his elderly uncle, [[Henry, King of Portugal|Cardinal Henry]], as his heir. This initiates a succession crisis in [[Portugal]].
*[[1693]] &amp;ndash; Date traditionally ascribed to [[Dom Perignon (person)|Dom Perignon]]'s invention of [[Champagne (wine)|Champagne]].
*[[1704]] &amp;ndash; [[War of the Spanish Succession]]: [[Gibraltar]] is captured by an [[England|English]] and [[Netherlands|Dutch]] fleet, commanded by [[Admiral]] Sir [[George Rooke]] and allied with [[Charles VI, Holy Roman Emperor|Archduke Charles]].
*[[1789]] &amp;ndash; In [[France]] members of the [[National Constituent Assembly]] take an oath to end [[feudalism]] and abandon their [[privileges]].
*[[1790]] &amp;ndash; A newly passed [[tariff]] act creates the ''[[Revenue Cutter Service]]'' (the forerunner of the [[United States Coast Guard]]).
*[[1791]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of Sistova]] is signed, ending the [[Ottoman-Habsburg wars]].
*[[1821]] &amp;ndash; Atkinson &amp; Alexander publish the ''[[The Saturday Evening Post|Saturday Evening Post]]'' for the first time as a weekly [[newspaper]].
*[[1824]] &amp;ndash; The Battle of [[Kos]] is fought between [[Ottoman Empire|Turk]] and [[Greece|Greek]] forces.
*[[1854]] &amp;ndash; The [[Flag of Japan|Hinomaru]] is established as the official flag to be flown from [[Japan]]ese ships.
*[[1863]] &amp;ndash; [[Matica slovenská]], [[Slovakia]]'s public-law cultural and scientific institution focusing on topics around the [[Slovaks|Slovak nation]], is established in [[Martin, Slovakia|Martin]].
*[[1873]] &amp;ndash; [[Indian Wars]]: whilst protecting a [[railroad]] survey party in [[Montana]], the [[U.S. 7th Cavalry Regiment|United States 7th Cavalry]], under [[Lieutenant colonel (United States)|Lieutenant Colonel]] [[George Armstrong Custer]] clashes for the first time with the [[Sioux]] near the [[Tongue River (Montana)|Tongue River]]; only one man on each side is killed.
*[[1892]] &amp;ndash; The parents of [[Lizzie Borden]] are found murdered in their [[Fall River, Massachusetts]] home.
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; The [[Greenwich foot tunnel]] under the [[River Thames]] opens.
*[[1906]] &amp;ndash; [[Central Railway Station, Sydney]] opens.
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: [[Germany]] invades [[Belgium]]. In response, the [[United Kingdom]] declares war on [[Germany]]. The [[United States]] declare their [[Neutral country|neutrality]].
*[[1916]] &amp;ndash; World War I: [[Liberia]] declares war on [[Germany]].
*[[1924]] &amp;ndash; [[Diplomatic relations]] between [[Mexico]] and the [[Soviet Union]] are established.
*[[1936]] &amp;ndash; [[List of Prime Ministers of Greece|Prime Minister of Greece]] [[Ioannis Metaxas]] suspends [[Hellenic Parliament|parliament]] and the [[Constitution of Greece|Constitution]] and establishes the [[4th of August Regime]].
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[The Holocaust]]: a tip from a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] informer leads the [[Gestapo]] to a sealed-off area in an [[Amsterdam]] warehouse where they find and arrest [[Jew]]ish [[diarist]] [[Anne Frank]], her family, and four others.
*[[1946]] &amp;ndash; An [[1946 Dominican Republic earthquake|earthquake of magnitude 8.0]] hits northern [[Dominican Republic]]. 100 are killed and 20,000 are left homeless.
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; The [[Supreme Court of Japan]] is established.
*[[1954]] &amp;ndash; The [[Government of Pakistan]] approves [[Qaumi Tarana]], written by Hafeez Jullundhry and composed by [[Ahmed Ghulamali Chagla]], as the [[national anthem]].
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; The [[Billboard Hot 100]] is founded.
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[American civil rights movement]]: [[civil rights]] workers [[Michael Schwerner]], [[Andrew Goodman]] and [[James Chaney]] are found dead in [[Mississippi]] after disappearing on [[June 21]].
*  1964   &amp;ndash; [[Gulf of Tonkin Incident]]: [[United States|U.S.]] [[destroyer]]s {{USS|Maddox|DD-731|6}} and {{USS|Turner Joy|DD-951|6}} report coming under attack in the [[Gulf of Tonkin]].
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; The [[Politics of the Cook Islands#Constitution|Constitution of Cook Islands]] comes into force, giving the [[Cook Islands]] self-governing status within [[New Zealand]].
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: at the apartment of [[France|French]] intermediary [[Jean Sainteny]] in [[Paris]], [[United States|American]] representative [[Henry Kissinger]] and [[North Vietnamese]] representative [[Xuan Thuy]] begin secret peace negotiations. The negotiations will eventually fail.
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; A [[Italicus Express bombing 1974|bomb]] explodes in  the ''Italicus Express'' train at [[San Benedetto Val di Sambro]], [[Italy]], killing 12 people and wounding 22.
*[[1975]] &amp;ndash; The [[Japanese Red Army]] takes [[1975 AIA building hostage crisis|more than 50 hostages]] at the AIA Building housing several embassies in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]]. The hostages include the [[United States|U.S.]] [[consul]] and the [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[chargé d’affaires]]. The gunmen win the release of five imprisoned comrades and fly with them to [[Libya]].
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[President of the United States|US President]] [[Jimmy Carter]] signs legislation creating the [[United States Department of Energy]].
*[[1984]] &amp;ndash; The [[Republic of Upper Volta]] changes its name to [[Burkina Faso]].
*[[1987]] &amp;ndash; The [[Federal Communications Commission]] rescinds the [[Fairness Doctrine]] which had required [[radio]] and [[television]] stations to present controversial issues &quot;fairly&quot;.
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; The [[Greece|Greek]] cruise ship {{Ship|MTS|Oceanos}} sinks off the [[Eastern Cape|Wild Coast]] of [[South Africa]].
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; A [[federal judge]] sentences [[Los Angeles Police Department|LAPD]] [[Police officer|officer]]s [[Stacey Koon]] and [[Laurence Powell]] to 30 months in prison for violating [[motorist]] [[Rodney King]]'s [[civil rights]].
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; [[Operation Storm]] begins in [[Croatia]].
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Soham murders]]: 10 year old school girls Jessica Chapman and Holly Wells go missing from the town of [[Soham]], [[Cambridgeshire]], [[United Kingdom]].
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Prime Minister of Canada|Prime Minister]] [[Paul Martin]] announces that [[Michaëlle Jean]] will be [[Canada]]'s 27th [[Governor General of Canada|Governor General]].
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; A [[2006 Trincomalee massacre of NGO workers|massacre]], is carried out by [[Sri Lankan]] government forces, killing 17 employees of the [[France|French]] [[INGO]] [[Action Against Hunger]] (known internationally as Action Contre la Faim, or ACF).
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[NASA]]'s [[Phoenix (spacecraft)|Phoenix]] spaceship is launched.
*  2007   &amp;ndash; Airport police officer [[María del Luján Telpuk]] discovers a suitcase containing the undeclared sum of [[US$]]800,000 as it goes through an [[x-ray machine]] in [[Aeroparque Jorge Newbery]] in [[Buenos Aires]], sparking an international scandal involving [[Venezuela]] and [[Argentina]] known as &quot;[[Maletinazo]]&quot;.
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[California]]'s [[California Proposition 8 (2008)|Proposition 8]], the ballot initiative prohibiting same-sex marriage passed by the state's voters in 2008, is overturned by Judge [[Vaughn Walker]] in the case [[Perry v. Schwarzenegger]].

